Karen Alexander (born 1946) was an American singer-songwriter who had some success in the 1970s.
In 1965, she married Esfandiar Bahrampour, an Iranian architect and moved to Tehran.
Her first album was Isn't It Always Love (1975).
Eventually, the situation became too dangerous and she fled with her family in 1979.
Bahrampour, Tara (1994) To see and see again: a life in Iran and America.
While Karen was living in Tehran she travelled back to the U.S., now and then.
Three years later she recorded her second and final album, Voyager.
